metadata.name: Ryokou #138
metadata.description:
Ryokou, the Japanese term for travel, marks the commencement of every journey, much like the initiation of this algorithm. I initially conceived this idea in "Tessera" and have since extended and incorporated it into various other artistic endeavors.

The canvas is versatile, offering over 40 color themes and even more potential combinations.

Press s in live mode for a PNG download
Press (1-5) to change resolution

Lammetje December 2023

metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #177
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‘Organic Matr’ (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


—— 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter’s wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‘scale’ parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.

metadata.name: Stargazer #24
metadata.description:
Stargazer seeking something out of dark sky.

Live view options:
- Press "s" key: Saves the image
- Press "f" key: Shows in fullscreen
- Press "1" to "4" key: Explores different scenes

Depending on the device / browser you run it on, it may take some time for the drawing to complete.
Made with p5js and shaders.

December 2022
ykxotkx

metadata.name: Artifice #157
metadata.description:
This series is is about playful obfuscation.

The fxtext article linked on the main profect goes more in-depth into what is meant by that, as well as the events that led to this collection.

5640 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries. Palettes make up a third of the code.

In live mode:
‘S’ : save as png (3000 × 3600)
’V’ : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=p’ : paper grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 9000 ×10600 (Chrome only, and may take a moment)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append “&g=p&h=t” to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save a png with those settings applied.

metadata.name: Proto alphabet #51
metadata.description:
For more than 4000 years, before Lineal A in Crete, proto alphabets were created. They freed man from the chains of evolution and gave a way to record the rhythm of the passage of time.

As recursion generates a grammar, recursion generates the strokes that shape the following proto alphabets, which attempt to record the passage of time.

Time is the substance I am made of. Time is a river which sweeps me along, but I am the river; it is a tiger which destroys me, but I am the tiger; it is a fire which consumes me, but I am the fire. - Jorge Luis Borges


Desde hace más de 4000 años, antes Lineal A en Creta, proto alfabetos fueron creados. Liberaron al hombre de las cadenas de la evolución y dieron una forma para registrar el ritmo del paso del tiempo.

Como la recursividad genera una gramática, la recursividad genera los trazos que dan forma a los siguientes proto alfabetos, los cuales intentan registrar el paso del tiempo.

El tiempo es la sustancia de que estoy hecho. El tiempo es un río que me arrebata, pero yo soy el río; es un tigre que me destroza, pero yo soy el tigre; es un fuego que me consume, pero yo soy el fuego. - Jorge Luis Borges


Controls (in live view):
- Press s to get a PNG file
- Press S to get a SVG file

Artwork by x0y0z0 @x0y0z0tn (2023)

metadata.name: Flow around #80
metadata.description:
Each object stretches and contracts to form a collective flow. And the flow changes with time.
Created using p5.js.

metadata.name: System α #137
metadata.description:
"To capture the fleeting time in the generating process."

In this work,I d'like focus on the generating of generative art system itself rather than imitate some scene or style.
And with the flow of time, try to figure out where it can take me toward.

This work would be a series of my alternative view on generative art.
"α" means the first step of this series.

Press [s] in live view to save file as PNG.
Press [p] to stop.

------
Happy first birthday fx(hash) !!

20% of primary revenues go to Savepakistan Flood Relief Fundraiser.
20% of primary revenues go to the Processing foundation.

metadata.name: Layers #30
metadata.description:
It's the first time I really delved into studying about P5JS

I spent the last one collecting generative art and it made my passion for all this just grow, as a collector I wanted to move forward and want to do something more and so developed this project. 

I've been a designer for almost 10 years, an art director for over 1 year, I work all day with design every day, Photoshop and its infinite layers haunt me all day, as my passion wanted to insert something related there in my work so I thought of "layers" and thus "Layers" was born, layers and layers, specifically of rectangles one on top of the other forming the interactions of this work.

5 Styles:

Dunes:
Curves, some sharp and others less so, some remind me of sand dunes.

moiree:
It reminds me a little of compositions with a Moiré effect, forming curves where there is the presence of shadows giving relief.

Arranged:

A style where there is a certain organization of lines, but not perfect.

Strips:

Strips of colors on top of each other.

Harmonic:
It forms flat compositions, they are more organized layers.


17 Color Palettes based on famous works such as paintings and compositions:

"Mondrian - Composition with Large Red Plane, Yellow, Black, Gray and Blue / Piet Mondrian"
"Monalisa - Leonardo da Vinci"
"Portrait - Van Gogh self-portrait / Van Gogh"
"Venus - The Birth of Venus / Sandro Botticelli"
"Memory - The Persistence of Memory / Salvador Dalí"
"Son - The Son of Man /René Magritte"
"Guitarist - The Old Guitarist / Pablo Picasso"
"Canna - Red Canna / Georgia O'Keeffe"
"Drowning - Drowning Girl / Roy Lichtenstein"
"American - American Gothic / Grant Wood"
"Sunrise - Impression, Sunrise / Claude Monet"
"Creation - The Creation of Adam / Michelangelo"
"Girl - Girl with a Pearl Earring / Johannes Vermeer"
"Square - Black Square / Kazimir Malevich"
"Wave - The Great Wave off Kanagawa / Katsushika Hokusai"
"Wanderer - Wanderer above the Sea of ​​Fog / David Friedrich"
"Scream - The Scream / Edvard Munch"

"Layers" uses grains/noises function by Gorilla Sun, thanks for sharing your article with us! Article https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain

Created with p5js / Alex Benedith

metadata.name: Hashed Cities #332
metadata.description:
This token generates a deterministic set of minimal, abstract buildings of varying widths, heights, transparencies, and patterns, assembling a skyline view of your own unique imaginary city. Each city comes with its own randomized city day.

Each mint has a native setting (Day or Night) which combined with the current time of viewing influences real-time movements of celestial bodies in your mint, e.g. on a mint with the Day setting, the sun will only appear when viewed during the day. The piece will re-render every minute.

The individual strokes of this token feature some of my latest developments of an algorithm that generatively simulates the texture of print imperfections. They are randomized at each render to give it a unique character. Note that depending on the complexity of each mint, some renders may introduce a brief pause. The aesthetics are greatly inspired by plotter art of early computer artists such as 'City Painting' by Grace C. Hertlein.

Made in p5js
Created Nov 2021
Artist: @Yazid

metadata.name: Lepidoptera #83
metadata.description:
I love trying to capture the textures and colors found in nature and reproduce them with code. Lepidoptera is inspired by the species of the same name.

Features include: color palette, medium hatching count, large hatching count, noise offset, and noise level.
